Multiple conditions with elif
Sometimes you need to check more than two possibilities. That is where elif comes in.

score = 75

if score &gt;= 90:
    print("Grade A")
elif score &gt;= 75:
    print("Grade B")
elif score &gt;= 60:
    print("Grade C")
else:
    print("Grade D")

Grade B


Python evaluates conditions from top to bottom at the first True condition
